1.00	Hitzacker	Hitzacker	Hitzacker is a town in the Lüchow-Dannenberg district of Lower Saxony, Germany. It is situated on the river Elbe, approx. 8 km north of Dannenberg, and 45 km east of Lüneburg. The 2007 population of Hitzacker was 4,982, and its postal code is 29456. The mayor is Karl Guhl. The town is located on the German Timber-Frame Road and is part of the Samtgemeinde ("collective municipality") of Elbtalaue.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0d/Germany_location_map.svg/170px-Germany_location_map.svg.png
